Preheat the oven to 200C/180C Fan/Gas 6. Put the sweet potato in a small roasting tray. Drizzle over the oil over, season with salt, pepper and the chilli flakes and rub in well. Put the chipolatas on top and roast for 15 minutes.Add the broccoli to the roasting tray, stir to make sure it gets coated in oil and bake for another 15â€“20 minutes, or until the sausages are cooked through, the sweet potato is tender and the broccoli is slightly charred. Serve.